2069/// ParseBuiltinPrimaryExpression
2070///
2071/// \verbatim
2072/// primary-expression: [C99 6.5.1]
2073/// [GNU] '__builtin_va_arg' '(' assignment-expression ',' type-name ')'
2074/// [GNU] '__builtin_offsetof' '(' type-name ',' offsetof-member-designator')'
2075/// [GNU] '__builtin_choose_expr' '(' assign-expr ',' assign-expr ','
2076/// assign-expr ')'
2077/// [GNU] '__builtin_types_compatible_p' '(' type-name ',' type-name ')'
2078/// [GNU] '__builtin_FILE' '(' ')'
2079/// [GNU] '__builtin_FUNCTION' '(' ')'
2080/// [GNU] '__builtin_LINE' '(' ')'
2081/// [CLANG] '__builtin_COLUMN' '(' ')'
2082/// [OCL] '__builtin_astype' '(' assignment-expression ',' type-name ')'
2083///
2084/// [GNU] offsetof-member-designator:
2085/// [GNU] identifier
2086/// [GNU] offsetof-member-designator '.' identifier
2087/// [GNU] offsetof-member-designator '[' expression ']'
2088/// \endverbatim
2089ExprResult Parser::ParseBuiltinPrimaryExpression() {
2090 ExprResult Res;
2091 const IdentifierInfo *BuiltinII = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
2092
2093 tok::TokenKind T = Tok.getKind();
2094 SourceLocation StartLoc = ConsumeToken(); // Eat the builtin identifier.
2095
2096 // All of these start with an open paren.
2097 if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_paren))
2098 return ExprError(Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected_after) << BuiltinII
2099 << tok::l_paren);
2100
2101 BalancedDelimiterTracker PT(*this, tok::l_paren);
2102 PT.consumeOpen();
2103
2104 // TODO: Build AST.
2105
2106 switch (T) {
2107 default: llvm_unreachable("Not a builtin primary expression!");
2108 case tok::kw___builtin_va_arg: {
2109 ExprResult Expr(ParseAssignmentExpression());
2110
2111 if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::comma)) {
2112 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2113 Expr = ExprError();
2114 }
2115
2116 TypeResult Ty = ParseTypeName();
2117
2118 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
2119 Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::r_paren;
2120 Expr = ExprError();
2121 }
2122
2123 if (Expr.isInvalid() || Ty.isInvalid())
2124 Res = ExprError();
2125 else
2126 Res = Actions.ActOnVAArg(StartLoc, Expr.get(), Ty.get(), ConsumeParen());
2127 break;
2128 }
2129 case tok::kw___builtin_offsetof: {
2130 SourceLocation TypeLoc = Tok.getLocation();
2131 TypeResult Ty = ParseTypeName();
2132 if (Ty.isInvalid()) {
2133 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2134 return ExprError();
2135 }
2136
2137 if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::comma)) {
2138 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2139 return ExprError();
2140 }
2141
2142 // We must have at least one identifier here.
2143 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
2144 Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::identifier;
2145 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2146 return ExprError();
2147 }
2148
2149 // Keep track of the various subcomponents we see.
2150 SmallVector<Sema::OffsetOfComponent, 4> Comps;
2151
2152 Comps.push_back(Sema::OffsetOfComponent());
2153 Comps.back().isBrackets = false;
2154 Comps.back().U.IdentInfo = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
2155 Comps.back().LocStart = Comps.back().LocEnd = ConsumeToken();
2156
2157 // FIXME: This loop leaks the index expressions on error.
2158 while (1) {
2159 if (Tok.is(tok::period)) {
2160 // offsetof-member-designator: offsetof-member-designator '.' identifier
2161 Comps.push_back(Sema::OffsetOfComponent());
2162 Comps.back().isBrackets = false;
2163 Comps.back().LocStart = ConsumeToken();
2164
2165 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
2166 Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::identifier;
2167 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2168 return ExprError();
2169 }
2170 Comps.back().U.IdentInfo = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
2171 Comps.back().LocEnd = ConsumeToken();
2172
2173 } else if (Tok.is(tok::l_square)) {
2174 if (CheckProhibitedCXX11Attribute())
2175 return ExprError();
2176
2177 // offsetof-member-designator: offsetof-member-design '[' expression ']'
2178 Comps.push_back(Sema::OffsetOfComponent());
2179 Comps.back().isBrackets = true;
2180 BalancedDelimiterTracker ST(*this, tok::l_square);
2181 ST.consumeOpen();
2182 Comps.back().LocStart = ST.getOpenLocation();
2183 Res = ParseExpression();
2184 if (Res.isInvalid()) {
2185 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2186 return Res;
2187 }
2188 Comps.back().U.E = Res.get();
2189
2190 ST.consumeClose();
2191 Comps.back().LocEnd = ST.getCloseLocation();
2192 } else {
2193 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
2194 PT.consumeClose();
2195 Res = ExprError();
2196 } else if (Ty.isInvalid()) {
2197 Res = ExprError();
2198 } else {
2199 PT.consumeClose();
2200 Res = Actions.ActOnBuiltinOffsetOf(getCurScope(), StartLoc, TypeLoc,
2201 Ty.get(), Comps,
2202 PT.getCloseLocation());
2203 }
2204 break;
2205 }
2206 }
2207 break;
2208 }
2209 case tok::kw___builtin_choose_expr: {
2210 ExprResult Cond(ParseAssignmentExpression());
2211 if (Cond.isInvalid()) {
2212 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2213 return Cond;
2214 }
2215 if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::comma)) {
2216 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2217 return ExprError();
2218 }
2219
2220 ExprResult Expr1(ParseAssignmentExpression());
2221 if (Expr1.isInvalid()) {
2222 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2223 return Expr1;
2224 }
2225 if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::comma)) {
2226 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2227 return ExprError();
2228 }
2229
2230 ExprResult Expr2(ParseAssignmentExpression());
2231 if (Expr2.isInvalid()) {
2232 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2233 return Expr2;
2234 }
2235 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
2236 Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::r_paren;
2237 return ExprError();
2238 }
2239 Res = Actions.ActOnChooseExpr(StartLoc, Cond.get(), Expr1.get(),
2240 Expr2.get(), ConsumeParen());
2241 break;
2242 }
2243 case tok::kw___builtin_astype: {
2244 // The first argument is an expression to be converted, followed by a comma.
2245 ExprResult Expr(ParseAssignmentExpression());
2246 if (Expr.isInvalid()) {
2247 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2248 return ExprError();
2249 }
2250
2251 if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::comma)) {
2252 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2253 return ExprError();
2254 }
2255
2256 // Second argument is the type to bitcast to.
2257 TypeResult DestTy = ParseTypeName();
2258 if (DestTy.isInvalid())
2259 return ExprError();
2260
2261 // Attempt to consume the r-paren.
2262 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
2263 Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::r_paren;
2264 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2265 return ExprError();
2266 }
2267
2268 Res = Actions.ActOnAsTypeExpr(Expr.get(), DestTy.get(), StartLoc,
2269 ConsumeParen());
2270 break;
2271 }
2272 case tok::kw___builtin_convertvector: {
2273 // The first argument is an expression to be converted, followed by a comma.
2274 ExprResult Expr(ParseAssignmentExpression());
2275 if (Expr.isInvalid()) {
2276 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2277 return ExprError();
2278 }
2279
2280 if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::comma)) {
2281 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2282 return ExprError();
2283 }
2284
2285 // Second argument is the type to bitcast to.
2286 TypeResult DestTy = ParseTypeName();
2287 if (DestTy.isInvalid())
2288 return ExprError();
2289
2290 // Attempt to consume the r-paren.
2291 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
2292 Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::r_paren;
2293 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2294 return ExprError();
2295 }
2296
2297 Res = Actions.ActOnConvertVectorExpr(Expr.get(), DestTy.get(), StartLoc,
2298 ConsumeParen());
2299 break;
2300 }
2301 case tok::kw___builtin_COLUMN:
2302 case tok::kw___builtin_FILE:
2303 case tok::kw___builtin_FUNCTION:
2304 case tok::kw___builtin_LINE: {
2305 // Attempt to consume the r-paren.
2306 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
2307 Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::r_paren;
2308 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2309 return ExprError();
2310 }
2311 SourceLocExpr::IdentKind Kind = [&] {
2312 switch (T) {
2313 case tok::kw___builtin_FILE:
2314 return SourceLocExpr::File;
2315 case tok::kw___builtin_FUNCTION:
2316 return SourceLocExpr::Function;
2317 case tok::kw___builtin_LINE:
2318 return SourceLocExpr::Line;
2319 case tok::kw___builtin_COLUMN:
2320 return SourceLocExpr::Column;
2321 default:
2322 llvm_unreachable("invalid keyword");
2323 }
2324 }();
2325 Res = Actions.ActOnSourceLocExpr(Kind, StartLoc, ConsumeParen());
2326 break;
2327 }
2328 }
2329
2330 if (Res.isInvalid())
2331 return ExprError();
2332
2333 // These can be followed by postfix-expr pieces because they are
2334 // primary-expressions.
2335 return ParsePostfixExpressionSuffix(Res.get());
2336}

2338/// ParseParenExpression - This parses the unit that starts with a '(' token,
2339/// based on what is allowed by ExprType. The actual thing parsed is returned
2340/// in ExprType. If stopIfCastExpr is true, it will only return the parsed type,
2341/// not the parsed cast-expression.
2342///
2343/// \verbatim
2344/// primary-expression: [C99 6.5.1]
2345/// '(' expression ')'
2346/// [GNU] '(' compound-statement ')' (if !ParenExprOnly)
2347/// postfix-expression: [C99 6.5.2]
2348/// '(' type-name ')' '{' initializer-list '}'
2349/// '(' type-name ')' '{' initializer-list ',' '}'
2350/// cast-expression: [C99 6.5.4]
2351/// '(' type-name ')' cast-expression
2352/// [ARC] bridged-cast-expression
2353/// [ARC] bridged-cast-expression:
2354/// (__bridge type-name) cast-expression
2355/// (__bridge_transfer type-name) cast-expression
2356/// (__bridge_retained type-name) cast-expression
2357/// fold-expression: [C++1z]
2358/// '(' cast-expression fold-operator '...' ')'
2359/// '(' '...' fold-operator cast-expression ')'
2360/// '(' cast-expression fold-operator '...'
2361/// fold-operator cast-expression ')'
2362/// \endverbatim
2363ExprResult
2364Parser::ParseParenExpression(ParenParseOption &ExprType, bool stopIfCastExpr,
2365 bool isTypeCast, ParsedType &CastTy,
2366 SourceLocation &RParenLoc) {
2367 assert(Tok.is(tok::l_paren) && "Not a paren expr!");
2368 ColonProtectionRAIIObject ColonProtection(*this, false);
2369 BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_paren);
2370 if (T.consumeOpen())
2371 return ExprError();
2372 SourceLocation OpenLoc = T.getOpenLocation();
2373
2374 PreferredType.enterParenExpr(Tok.getLocation(), OpenLoc);
2375
2376 ExprResult Result(true);
2377 bool isAmbiguousTypeId;
2378 CastTy = nullptr;
2379
2380 if (Tok.is(tok::code_completion)) {
2381 Actions.CodeCompleteExpression(
2382 getCurScope(), PreferredType.get(Tok.getLocation()),
2383 /*IsParenthesized=*/ExprType >= CompoundLiteral);
2384 cutOffParsing();
2385 return ExprError();
2386 }
2387
2388 // Diagnose use of bridge casts in non-arc mode.
2389 bool BridgeCast = (getLangOpts().ObjC &&
2390 Tok.isOneOf(tok::kw___bridge,
2391 tok::kw___bridge_transfer,
2392 tok::kw___bridge_retained,
2393 tok::kw___bridge_retain));
2394 if (BridgeCast && !getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount) {
2395 if (!TryConsumeToken(tok::kw___bridge)) {
2396 StringRef BridgeCastName = Tok.getName();
2397 SourceLocation BridgeKeywordLoc = ConsumeToken();
2398 if (!PP.getSourceManager().isInSystemHeader(BridgeKeywordLoc))
2399 Diag(BridgeKeywordLoc, diag::warn_arc_bridge_cast_nonarc)
2400 << BridgeCastName
2401 << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(BridgeKeywordLoc, "");
2402 }
2403 BridgeCast = false;
2404 }
2405
2406 // None of these cases should fall through with an invalid Result
2407 // unless they've already reported an error.
2408 if (ExprType >= CompoundStmt && Tok.is(tok::l_brace)) {
2409 Diag(Tok, diag::ext_gnu_statement_expr);
2410
2411 if (!getCurScope()->getFnParent() && !getCurScope()->getBlockParent()) {
2412 Result = ExprError(Diag(OpenLoc, diag::err_stmtexpr_file_scope));
2413 } else {
2414 // Find the nearest non-record decl context. Variables declared in a
2415 // statement expression behave as if they were declared in the enclosing
2416 // function, block, or other code construct.
2417 DeclContext *CodeDC = Actions.CurContext;
2418 while (CodeDC->isRecord() || isa<EnumDecl>(CodeDC)) {
2419 CodeDC = CodeDC->getParent();
2420 assert(CodeDC && !CodeDC->isFileContext() &&
2421 "statement expr not in code context");
2422 }
2423 Sema::ContextRAII SavedContext(Actions, CodeDC, /*NewThisContext=*/false);
2424
2425 Actions.ActOnStartStmtExpr();
2426
2427 StmtResult Stmt(ParseCompoundStatement(true));
2428 ExprType = CompoundStmt;
2429
2430 // If the substmt parsed correctly, build the AST node.
2431 if (!Stmt.isInvalid()) {
2432 Result = Actions.ActOnStmtExpr(OpenLoc, Stmt.get(), Tok.getLocation());
2433 } else {
2434 Actions.ActOnStmtExprError();
2435 }
2436 }
2437 } else if (ExprType >= CompoundLiteral && BridgeCast) {
2438 tok::TokenKind tokenKind = Tok.getKind();
2439 SourceLocation BridgeKeywordLoc = ConsumeToken();
2440
2441 // Parse an Objective-C ARC ownership cast expression.
2442 ObjCBridgeCastKind Kind;
2443 if (tokenKind == tok::kw___bridge)
2444 Kind = OBC_Bridge;
2445 else if (tokenKind == tok::kw___bridge_transfer)
2446 Kind = OBC_BridgeTransfer;
2447 else if (tokenKind == tok::kw___bridge_retained)
2448 Kind = OBC_BridgeRetained;
2449 else {
2450 // As a hopefully temporary workaround, allow __bridge_retain as
2451 // a synonym for __bridge_retained, but only in system headers.
2452 assert(tokenKind == tok::kw___bridge_retain);
2453 Kind = OBC_BridgeRetained;
2454 if (!PP.getSourceManager().isInSystemHeader(BridgeKeywordLoc))
2455 Diag(BridgeKeywordLoc, diag::err_arc_bridge_retain)
2456 << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(BridgeKeywordLoc,
2457 "__bridge_retained");
2458 }
2459
2460 TypeResult Ty = ParseTypeName();
2461 T.consumeClose();
2462 ColonProtection.restore();
2463 RParenLoc = T.getCloseLocation();
2464
2465 PreferredType.enterTypeCast(Tok.getLocation(), Ty.get().get());
2466 ExprResult SubExpr = ParseCastExpression(/*isUnaryExpression=*/false);
2467
2468 if (Ty.isInvalid() || SubExpr.isInvalid())
2469 return ExprError();
2470
2471 return Actions.ActOnObjCBridgedCast(getCurScope(), OpenLoc, Kind,
2472 BridgeKeywordLoc, Ty.get(),
2473 RParenLoc, SubExpr.get());
2474 } else if (Tok.isOneOf(tok::kw___cheri_fromcap, tok::kw___cheri_tocap,
2475 tok::kw___cheri_offset, tok::kw___cheri_addr,
2476 tok::kw___cheri_cast)) {
2477 // TODO: (__cheri_bounded_cast struct foo[42])?
2478 tok::TokenKind tokenKind = Tok.getKind();
2479 SourceLocation CheriKeywordLoc = ConsumeToken();
2480
2481 // Parse a CHERI ptr, offset or address cast
2482 TypeResult Ty = ParseTypeName();
2483 T.consumeClose();
2484 ColonProtection.restore();
2485 RParenLoc = T.getCloseLocation();
2486 ExprResult SubExpr = ParseCastExpression(/*isUnaryExpression=*/false);
2487
2488 if (Ty.isInvalid() || SubExpr.isInvalid())
2489 return ExprError();
2490
2491 return Actions.ActOnCheriCast(getCurScope(), OpenLoc, tokenKind,
2492 CheriKeywordLoc, Ty.get(),
2493 RParenLoc, SubExpr.get());
2494 } else if (ExprType >= CompoundLiteral &&
2495 isTypeIdInParens(isAmbiguousTypeId)) {
2496
2497 // Otherwise, this is a compound literal expression or cast expression.
2498
2499 // In C++, if the type-id is ambiguous we disambiguate based on context.
2500 // If stopIfCastExpr is true the context is a typeof/sizeof/alignof
2501 // in which case we should treat it as type-id.
2502 // if stopIfCastExpr is false, we need to determine the context past the
2503 // parens, so we defer to ParseCXXAmbiguousParenExpression for that.
2504 if (isAmbiguousTypeId && !stopIfCastExpr) {
2505 ExprResult res = ParseCXXAmbiguousParenExpression(ExprType, CastTy, T,
2506 ColonProtection);
2507 RParenLoc = T.getCloseLocation();
2508 return res;
2509 }
2510
2511 // Parse the type declarator.
2512 DeclSpec DS(AttrFactory);
2513 ParseSpecifierQualifierList(DS);
2514 Declarator DeclaratorInfo(DS, DeclaratorContext::TypeNameContext);
2515 ParseDeclarator(DeclaratorInfo);
2516
2517 // If our type is followed by an identifier and either ':' or ']', then
2518 // this is probably an Objective-C message send where the leading '[' is
2519 // missing. Recover as if that were the case.
2520 if (!DeclaratorInfo.isInvalidType() && Tok.is(tok::identifier) &&
2521 !InMessageExpression && getLangOpts().ObjC &&
2522 (NextToken().is(tok::colon) || NextToken().is(tok::r_square))) {
2523 TypeResult Ty;
2524 {
2525 InMessageExpressionRAIIObject InMessage(*this, false);
2526 Ty = Actions.ActOnTypeName(getCurScope(), DeclaratorInfo);
2527 }
2528 Result = ParseObjCMessageExpressionBody(SourceLocation(),
2529 SourceLocation(),
2530 Ty.get(), nullptr);
2531 } else {
2532 // Match the ')'.
2533 T.consumeClose();
2534 ColonProtection.restore();
2535 RParenLoc = T.getCloseLocation();
2536 if (Tok.is(tok::l_brace)) {
2537 ExprType = CompoundLiteral;
2538 TypeResult Ty;
2539 {
2540 InMessageExpressionRAIIObject InMessage(*this, false);
2541 Ty = Actions.ActOnTypeName(getCurScope(), DeclaratorInfo);
2542 }
2543 return ParseCompoundLiteralExpression(Ty.get(), OpenLoc, RParenLoc);
2544 }
2545
2546 if (Tok.is(tok::l_paren)) {
2547 // This could be OpenCL vector Literals
2548 if (getLangOpts().OpenCL)
2549 {
2550 TypeResult Ty;
2551 {
2552 InMessageExpressionRAIIObject InMessage(*this, false);
2553 Ty = Actions.ActOnTypeName(getCurScope(), DeclaratorInfo);
2554 }
2555 if(Ty.isInvalid())
2556 {
2557 return ExprError();
2558 }
2559 QualType QT = Ty.get().get().getCanonicalType();
2560 if (QT->isVectorType())
2561 {
2562 // We parsed '(' vector-type-name ')' followed by '('
2563
2564 // Parse the cast-expression that follows it next.
2565 // isVectorLiteral = true will make sure we don't parse any
2566 // Postfix expression yet
2567 Result = ParseCastExpression(/*isUnaryExpression=*/false,
2568 /*isAddressOfOperand=*/false,
2569 /*isTypeCast=*/IsTypeCast,
2570 /*isVectorLiteral=*/true);
2571
2572 if (!Result.isInvalid()) {
2573 Result = Actions.ActOnCastExpr(getCurScope(), OpenLoc,
2574 DeclaratorInfo, CastTy,
2575 RParenLoc, Result.get());
2576 }
2577
2578 // After we performed the cast we can check for postfix-expr pieces.
2579 if (!Result.isInvalid()) {
2580 Result = ParsePostfixExpressionSuffix(Result);
2581 }
2582
2583 return Result;
2584 }
2585 }
2586 }
2587
2588 if (ExprType == CastExpr) {
2589 // We parsed '(' type-name ')' and the thing after it wasn't a '{'.
2590
2591 if (DeclaratorInfo.isInvalidType())
2592 return ExprError();
2593
2594 // Note that this doesn't parse the subsequent cast-expression, it just
2595 // returns the parsed type to the callee.
2596 if (stopIfCastExpr) {
2597 TypeResult Ty;
2598 {
2599 InMessageExpressionRAIIObject InMessage(*this, false);
2600 Ty = Actions.ActOnTypeName(getCurScope(), DeclaratorInfo);
2601 }
2602 CastTy = Ty.get();
2603 return ExprResult();
2604 }
2605
2606 // Reject the cast of super idiom in ObjC.
2607 if (Tok.is(tok::identifier) && getLangOpts().ObjC &&
2608 Tok.getIdentifierInfo() == Ident_super &&
2609 getCurScope()->isInObjcMethodScope() &&
2610 GetLookAheadToken(1).isNot(tok::period)) {
2611 Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_illegal_super_cast)
2612 << SourceRange(OpenLoc, RParenLoc);
2613 return ExprError();
2614 }
2615
2616 PreferredType.enterTypeCast(Tok.getLocation(), CastTy.get());
2617 // Parse the cast-expression that follows it next.
2618 // TODO: For cast expression with CastTy.
2619 Result = ParseCastExpression(/*isUnaryExpression=*/false,
2620 /*isAddressOfOperand=*/false,
2621 /*isTypeCast=*/IsTypeCast);
2622 if (!Result.isInvalid()) {
2623 Result = Actions.ActOnCastExpr(getCurScope(), OpenLoc,
2624 DeclaratorInfo, CastTy,
2625 RParenLoc, Result.get());
2626 }
2627 return Result;
2628 }
2629
2630 Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected_lbrace_in_compound_literal);
2631 return ExprError();
2632 }
2633 } else if (ExprType >= FoldExpr && Tok.is(tok::ellipsis) &&
2634 isFoldOperator(NextToken().getKind())) {
2635 ExprType = FoldExpr;
2636 return ParseFoldExpression(ExprResult(), T);
2637 } else if (isTypeCast) {
2638 // Parse the expression-list.
2639 InMessageExpressionRAIIObject InMessage(*this, false);
2640
2641 ExprVector ArgExprs;
2642 CommaLocsTy CommaLocs;
2643
2644 if (!ParseSimpleExpressionList(ArgExprs, CommaLocs)) {
2645 // FIXME: If we ever support comma expressions as operands to
2646 // fold-expressions, we'll need to allow multiple ArgExprs here.
2647 if (ExprType >= FoldExpr && ArgExprs.size() == 1 &&
2648 isFoldOperator(Tok.getKind()) && NextToken().is(tok::ellipsis)) {
2649 ExprType = FoldExpr;
2650 return ParseFoldExpression(ArgExprs[0], T);
2651 }
2652
2653 ExprType = SimpleExpr;
2654 Result = Actions.ActOnParenListExpr(OpenLoc, Tok.getLocation(),
2655 ArgExprs);
2656 }
2657 } else {
2658 InMessageExpressionRAIIObject InMessage(*this, false);
2659
2660 Result = ParseExpression(MaybeTypeCast);
2661 if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && MaybeTypeCast && Result.isUsable()) {
2662 // Correct typos in non-C++ code earlier so that implicit-cast-like
2663 // expressions are parsed correctly.
2664 Result = Actions.CorrectDelayedTyposInExpr(Result);
2665 }
2666
2667 if (ExprType >= FoldExpr && isFoldOperator(Tok.getKind()) &&
2668 NextToken().is(tok::ellipsis)) {
2669 ExprType = FoldExpr;
2670 return ParseFoldExpression(Result, T);
2671 }
2672 ExprType = SimpleExpr;
2673
2674 // Don't build a paren expression unless we actually match a ')'.
2675 if (!Result.isInvalid() && Tok.is(tok::r_paren))
2676 Result =
2677 Actions.ActOnParenExpr(OpenLoc, Tok.getLocation(), Result.get());
2678 }
2679
2680 // Match the ')'.
2681 if (Result.isInvalid()) {
2682 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2683 return ExprError();
2684 }
2685
2686 T.consumeClose();
2687 RParenLoc = T.getCloseLocation();
2688 return Result;
2689}

2691/// ParseCompoundLiteralExpression - We have parsed the parenthesized type-name
2692/// and we are at the left brace.
2693///
2694/// \verbatim
2695/// postfix-expression: [C99 6.5.2]
2696/// '(' type-name ')' '{' initializer-list '}'
2697/// '(' type-name ')' '{' initializer-list ',' '}'
2698/// \endverbatim
2699ExprResult
2700Parser::ParseCompoundLiteralExpression(ParsedType Ty,
2701 SourceLocation LParenLoc,
2702 SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
2703 assert(Tok.is(tok::l_brace) && "Not a compound literal!");
2704 if (!getLangOpts().C99) // Compound literals don't exist in C90.
2705 Diag(LParenLoc, diag::ext_c99_compound_literal);
2706 ExprResult Result = ParseInitializer();
2707 if (!Result.isInvalid() && Ty)
2708 return Actions.ActOnCompoundLiteral(LParenLoc, Ty, RParenLoc, Result.get());
2709 return Result;
2710}

2712/// ParseStringLiteralExpression - This handles the various token types that
2713/// form string literals, and also handles string concatenation [C99 5.1.1.2,
2714/// translation phase #6].
2715///
2716/// \verbatim
2717/// primary-expression: [C99 6.5.1]
2718/// string-literal
2719/// \verbatim
2720ExprResult Parser::ParseStringLiteralExpression(bool AllowUserDefinedLiteral) {
2721 assert(isTokenStringLiteral() && "Not a string literal!");
2722
2723 // String concat. Note that keywords like __func__ and __FUNCTION__ are not
2724 // considered to be strings for concatenation purposes.
2725 SmallVector<Token, 4> StringToks;
2726
2727 do {
2728 StringToks.push_back(Tok);
2729 ConsumeStringToken();
2730 } while (isTokenStringLiteral());
2731
2732 // Pass the set of string tokens, ready for concatenation, to the actions.
2733 return Actions.ActOnStringLiteral(StringToks,
2734 AllowUserDefinedLiteral ? getCurScope()
2735 : nullptr);
2736}

2738/// ParseGenericSelectionExpression - Parse a C11 generic-selection
2739/// [C11 6.5.1.1].
2740///
2741/// \verbatim
2742/// generic-selection:
2743/// _Generic ( assignment-expression , generic-assoc-list )
2744/// generic-assoc-list:
2745/// generic-association
2746/// generic-assoc-list , generic-association
2747/// generic-association:
2748/// type-name : assignment-expression
2749/// default : assignment-expression
2750/// \endverbatim
2751ExprResult Parser::ParseGenericSelectionExpression() {
2752 assert(Tok.is(tok::kw__Generic) && "_Generic keyword expected");
2753 SourceLocation KeyLoc = ConsumeToken();
2754
2755 if (!getLangOpts().C11)
2756 Diag(KeyLoc, diag::ext_c11_generic_selection);
2757
2758 BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_paren);
2759 if (T.expectAndConsume())
2760 return ExprError();
2761
2762 ExprResult ControllingExpr;
2763 {
2764 // C11 6.5.1.1p3 "The controlling expression of a generic selection is
2765 // not evaluated."
2766 EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
2767 Actions, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
2768 ControllingExpr =
2769 Actions.CorrectDelayedTyposInExpr(ParseAssignmentExpression());
2770 if (ControllingExpr.isInvalid()) {
2771 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2772 return ExprError();
2773 }
2774 }
2775
2776 if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::comma)) {
2777 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2778 return ExprError();
2779 }
2780
2781 SourceLocation DefaultLoc;
2782 TypeVector Types;
2783 ExprVector Exprs;
2784 do {
2785 ParsedType Ty;
2786 if (Tok.is(tok::kw_default)) {
2787 // C11 6.5.1.1p2 "A generic selection shall have no more than one default
2788 // generic association."
2789 if (!DefaultLoc.isInvalid()) {
2790 Diag(Tok, diag::err_duplicate_default_assoc);
2791 Diag(DefaultLoc, diag::note_previous_default_assoc);
2792 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2793 return ExprError();
2794 }
2795 DefaultLoc = ConsumeToken();
2796 Ty = nullptr;
2797 } else {
2798 ColonProtectionRAIIObject X(*this);
2799 TypeResult TR = ParseTypeName();
2800 if (TR.isInvalid()) {
2801 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2802 return ExprError();
2803 }
2804 Ty = TR.get();
2805 }
2806 Types.push_back(Ty);
2807
2808 if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::colon)) {
2809 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2810 return ExprError();
2811 }
2812
2813 // FIXME: These expressions should be parsed in a potentially potentially
2814 // evaluated context.
2815 ExprResult ER(
2816 Actions.CorrectDelayedTyposInExpr(ParseAssignmentExpression()));
2817 if (ER.isInvalid()) {
2818 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
2819 return ExprError();
2820 }
2821 Exprs.push_back(ER.get());
2822 } while (TryConsumeToken(tok::comma));
2823
2824 T.consumeClose();
2825 if (T.getCloseLocation().isInvalid())
2826 return ExprError();
2827
2828 return Actions.ActOnGenericSelectionExpr(KeyLoc, DefaultLoc,
2829 T.getCloseLocation(),
2830 ControllingExpr.get(),
2831 Types, Exprs);
2832}

2834/// Parse A C++1z fold-expression after the opening paren and optional
2835/// left-hand-side expression.
2836///
2837/// \verbatim
2838/// fold-expression:
2839/// ( cast-expression fold-operator ... )
2840/// ( ... fold-operator cast-expression )
2841/// ( cast-expression fold-operator ... fold-operator cast-expression )
2842ExprResult Parser::ParseFoldExpression(ExprResult LHS,
2843 BalancedDelimiterTracker &T) {
2844 if (LHS.isInvalid()) {
2845 T.skipToEnd();
2846 return true;
2847 }
2848
2849 tok::TokenKind Kind = tok::unknown;
2850 SourceLocation FirstOpLoc;
2851 if (LHS.isUsable()) {
2852 Kind = Tok.getKind();
2853 assert(isFoldOperator(Kind) && "missing fold-operator");
2854 FirstOpLoc = ConsumeToken();
2855 }
2856
2857 assert(Tok.is(tok::ellipsis) && "not a fold-expression");
2858 SourceLocation EllipsisLoc = ConsumeToken();
2859
2860 ExprResult RHS;
2861 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
2862 if (!isFoldOperator(Tok.getKind()))
2863 return Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_expected_fold_operator);
2864
2865 if (Kind != tok::unknown && Tok.getKind() != Kind)
2866 Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_fold_operator_mismatch)
2867 << SourceRange(FirstOpLoc);
2868 Kind = Tok.getKind();
2869 ConsumeToken();
2870
2871 RHS = ParseExpression();
2872 if (RHS.isInvalid()) {
2873 T.skipToEnd();
2874 return true;
2875 }
2876 }
2877
2878 Diag(EllipsisLoc, getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17
2879 ? diag::warn_cxx14_compat_fold_expression
2880 : diag::ext_fold_expression);
2881
2882 T.consumeClose();
2883 return Actions.ActOnCXXFoldExpr(T.getOpenLocation(), LHS.get(), Kind,
2884 EllipsisLoc, RHS.get(), T.getCloseLocation());
2885}

2887/// ParseExpressionList - Used for C/C++ (argument-)expression-list.
2888///
2889/// \verbatim
2890/// argument-expression-list:
2891/// assignment-expression
2892/// argument-expression-list , assignment-expression
2893///
2894/// [C++] expression-list:
2895/// [C++] assignment-expression
2896/// [C++] expression-list , assignment-expression
2897///
2898/// [C++0x] expression-list:
2899/// [C++0x] initializer-list
2900///
2901/// [C++0x] initializer-list
2902/// [C++0x] initializer-clause ...[opt]
2903/// [C++0x] initializer-list , initializer-clause ...[opt]
2904///
2905/// [C++0x] initializer-clause:
2906/// [C++0x] assignment-expression
2907/// [C++0x] braced-init-list
2908/// \endverbatim
2909bool Parser::ParseExpressionList(SmallVectorImpl<Expr *> &Exprs,
2910 SmallVectorImpl<SourceLocation> &CommaLocs,
2911 llvm::function_ref<void()> ExpressionStarts) {
2912 bool SawError = false;
2913 while (1) {
2914 if (ExpressionStarts)
2915 ExpressionStarts();
2916
2917 ExprResult Expr;
2918 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && Tok.is(tok::l_brace)) {
2919 Diag(Tok, diag::warn_cxx98_compat_generalized_initializer_lists);
2920 Expr = ParseBraceInitializer();
2921 } else
2922 Expr = ParseAssignmentExpression();
2923
2924 if (Tok.is(tok::ellipsis))
2925 Expr = Actions.ActOnPackExpansion(Expr.get(), ConsumeToken());
2926 if (Expr.isInvalid()) {
2927 SkipUntil(tok::comma, tok::r_paren, StopBeforeMatch);
2928 SawError = true;
2929 } else {
2930 Exprs.push_back(Expr.get());
2931 }
2932
2933 if (Tok.isNot(tok::comma))
2934 break;
2935 // Move to the next argument, remember where the comma was.
2936 Token Comma = Tok;
2937 CommaLocs.push_back(ConsumeToken());
2938
2939 checkPotentialAngleBracketDelimiter(Comma);
2940 }
2941 if (SawError) {
2942 // Ensure typos get diagnosed when errors were encountered while parsing the
2943 // expression list.
2944 for (auto &E : Exprs) {
2945 ExprResult Expr = Actions.CorrectDelayedTyposInExpr(E);
2946 if (Expr.isUsable()) E = Expr.get();
2947 }
2948 }
2949 return SawError;
2950}
2951
2952/// ParseSimpleExpressionList - A simple comma-separated list of expressions,
2953/// used for misc language extensions.
2954///
2955/// \verbatim
2956/// simple-expression-list:
2957/// assignment-expression
2958/// simple-expression-list , assignment-expression
2959/// \endverbatim
2960bool
2961Parser::ParseSimpleExpressionList(SmallVectorImpl<Expr*> &Exprs,
2962 SmallVectorImpl<SourceLocation> &CommaLocs) {
2963 while (1) {
2964 ExprResult Expr = ParseAssignmentExpression();
2965 if (Expr.isInvalid())
2966 return true;
2967
2968 Exprs.push_back(Expr.get());
2969
2970 if (Tok.isNot(tok::comma))
2971 return false;
2972
2973 // Move to the next argument, remember where the comma was.
2974 Token Comma = Tok;
2975 CommaLocs.push_back(ConsumeToken());
2976
2977 checkPotentialAngleBracketDelimiter(Comma);
2978 }
2979}

2981/// ParseBlockId - Parse a block-id, which roughly looks like int (int x).
2982///
2983/// \verbatim
2984/// [clang] block-id:
2985/// [clang] specifier-qualifier-list block-declarator
2986/// \endverbatim
2987void Parser::ParseBlockId(SourceLocation CaretLoc) {
2988 if (Tok.is(tok::code_completion)) {
2989 Actions.CodeCompleteOrdinaryName(getCurScope(), Sema::PCC_Type);
2990 return cutOffParsing();
2991 }
2992
2993 // Parse the specifier-qualifier-list piece.
2994 DeclSpec DS(AttrFactory);
2995 ParseSpecifierQualifierList(DS);
2996
2997 // Parse the block-declarator.
2998 Declarator DeclaratorInfo(DS, DeclaratorContext::BlockLiteralContext);
2999 DeclaratorInfo.setFunctionDefinitionKind(FDK_Definition);
3000 ParseDeclarator(DeclaratorInfo);
3001
3002 MaybeParseGNUAttributes(DeclaratorInfo);
3003
3004 // Inform sema that we are starting a block.
3005 Actions.ActOnBlockArguments(CaretLoc, DeclaratorInfo, getCurScope());
3006}
3007
3008/// ParseBlockLiteralExpression - Parse a block literal, which roughly looks
3009/// like ^(int x){ return x+1; }
3010///
3011/// \verbatim
3012/// block-literal:
3013/// [clang] '^' block-args[opt] compound-statement
3014/// [clang] '^' block-id compound-statement
3015/// [clang] block-args:
3016/// [clang] '(' parameter-list ')'
3017/// \endverbatim
3018ExprResult Parser::ParseBlockLiteralExpression() {
3019 assert(Tok.is(tok::caret) && "block literal starts with ^");
3020 SourceLocation CaretLoc = ConsumeToken();
3021
3022 PrettyStackTraceLoc CrashInfo(PP.getSourceManager(), CaretLoc,
3023 "block literal parsing");
3024
3025 // Enter a scope to hold everything within the block. This includes the
3026 // argument decls, decls within the compound expression, etc. This also
3027 // allows determining whether a variable reference inside the block is
3028 // within or outside of the block.
3029 ParseScope BlockScope(this, Scope::BlockScope | Scope::FnScope |
3030 Scope::CompoundStmtScope | Scope::DeclScope);
3031
3032 // Inform sema that we are starting a block.
3033 Actions.ActOnBlockStart(CaretLoc, getCurScope());
3034
3035 // Parse the return type if present.
3036 DeclSpec DS(AttrFactory);
3037 Declarator ParamInfo(DS, DeclaratorContext::BlockLiteralContext);
3038 ParamInfo.setFunctionDefinitionKind(FDK_Definition);
3039 // FIXME: Since the return type isn't actually parsed, it can't be used to
3040 // fill ParamInfo with an initial valid range, so do it manually.
3041 ParamInfo.SetSourceRange(SourceRange(Tok.getLocation(), Tok.getLocation()));
3042
3043 // If this block has arguments, parse them. There is no ambiguity here with
3044 // the expression case, because the expression case requires a parameter list.
3045 if (Tok.is(tok::l_paren)) {
3046 ParseParenDeclarator(ParamInfo);
3047 // Parse the pieces after the identifier as if we had "int(...)".
3048 // SetIdentifier sets the source range end, but in this case we're past
3049 // that location.
3050 SourceLocation Tmp = ParamInfo.getSourceRange().getEnd();
3051 ParamInfo.SetIdentifier(nullptr, CaretLoc);
3052 ParamInfo.SetRangeEnd(Tmp);
3053 if (ParamInfo.isInvalidType()) {
3054 // If there was an error parsing the arguments, they may have
3055 // tried to use ^(x+y) which requires an argument list. Just
3056 // skip the whole block literal.
3057 Actions.ActOnBlockError(CaretLoc, getCurScope());
3058 return ExprError();
3059 }
3060
3061 MaybeParseGNUAttributes(ParamInfo);
3062
3063 // Inform sema that we are starting a block.
3064 Actions.ActOnBlockArguments(CaretLoc, ParamInfo, getCurScope());
3065 } else if (!Tok.is(tok::l_brace)) {
3066 ParseBlockId(CaretLoc);
3067 } else {
3068 // Otherwise, pretend we saw (void).
3069 SourceLocation NoLoc;
3070 ParamInfo.AddTypeInfo(
3071 DeclaratorChunk::getFunction(/*HasProto=*/true,
3072 /*IsAmbiguous=*/false,
3073 /*RParenLoc=*/NoLoc,
3074 /*ArgInfo=*/nullptr,
3075 /*NumArgs=*/0,
3076 /*EllipsisLoc=*/NoLoc,
3077 /*RParenLoc=*/NoLoc,
3078 /*RefQualifierIsLvalueRef=*/true,
3079 /*RefQualifierLoc=*/NoLoc,
3080 /*MutableLoc=*/NoLoc, EST_None,
3081 /*ESpecRange=*/SourceRange(),
3082 /*Exceptions=*/nullptr,
3083 /*ExceptionRanges=*/nullptr,
3084 /*NumExceptions=*/0,
3085 /*NoexceptExpr=*/nullptr,
3086 /*ExceptionSpecTokens=*/nullptr,
3087 /*DeclsInPrototype=*/None, CaretLoc,
3088 CaretLoc, ParamInfo),
3089 CaretLoc);
3090
3091 MaybeParseGNUAttributes(ParamInfo);
3092
3093 // Inform sema that we are starting a block.
3094 Actions.ActOnBlockArguments(CaretLoc, ParamInfo, getCurScope());
3095 }
3096
3097
3098 ExprResult Result(true);
3099 if (!Tok.is(tok::l_brace)) {
3100 // Saw something like: ^expr
3101 Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected_expression);
3102 Actions.ActOnBlockError(CaretLoc, getCurScope());
3103 return ExprError();
3104 }
3105
3106 StmtResult Stmt(ParseCompoundStatementBody());
3107 BlockScope.Exit();
3108 if (!Stmt.isInvalid())

3124/// Validate availability spec list, emitting diagnostics if necessary. Returns
3125/// true if invalid.
3126static bool CheckAvailabilitySpecList(Parser &P,
3127 ArrayRef<AvailabilitySpec> AvailSpecs) {
3128 llvm::SmallSet<StringRef, 4> Platforms;
3129 bool HasOtherPlatformSpec = false;
3130 bool Valid = true;
3131 for (const auto &Spec : AvailSpecs) {
3132 if (Spec.isOtherPlatformSpec()) {
3133 if (HasOtherPlatformSpec) {
3134 P.Diag(Spec.getBeginLoc(), diag::err_availability_query_repeated_star);
3135 Valid = false;
3136 }
3137
3138 HasOtherPlatformSpec = true;
3139 continue;
3140 }
3141
3142 bool Inserted = Platforms.insert(Spec.getPlatform()).second;
3143 if (!Inserted) {
3144 // Rule out multiple version specs referring to the same platform.
3145 // For example, we emit an error for:
3146 // @available(macos 10.10, macos 10.11, *)
3147 StringRef Platform = Spec.getPlatform();
3148 P.Diag(Spec.getBeginLoc(), diag::err_availability_query_repeated_platform)
3149 << Spec.getEndLoc() << Platform;
3150 Valid = false;
3151 }
3152 }
3153
3154 if (!HasOtherPlatformSpec) {
3155 SourceLocation InsertWildcardLoc = AvailSpecs.back().getEndLoc();
3156 P.Diag(InsertWildcardLoc, diag::err_availability_query_wildcard_required)
3157 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(InsertWildcardLoc, ", *");
3158 return true;
3159 }
3160
3161 return !Valid;
3162}

3164/// Parse availability query specification.
3165///
3166/// availability-spec:
3167/// '*'
3168/// identifier version-tuple
3169Optional<AvailabilitySpec> Parser::ParseAvailabilitySpec() {
3170 if (Tok.is(tok::star)) {
3171 return AvailabilitySpec(ConsumeToken());
3172 } else {
3173 // Parse the platform name.
3174 if (Tok.is(tok::code_completion)) {
3175 Actions.CodeCompleteAvailabilityPlatformName();
3176 cutOffParsing();
3177 return None;
3178 }
3179 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
3180 Diag(Tok, diag::err_avail_query_expected_platform_name);
3181 return None;
3182 }
3183
3184 IdentifierLoc *PlatformIdentifier = ParseIdentifierLoc();
3185 SourceRange VersionRange;
3186 VersionTuple Version = ParseVersionTuple(VersionRange);
3187
3188 if (Version.empty())
3189 return None;
3190
3191 StringRef GivenPlatform = PlatformIdentifier->Ident->getName();
3192 StringRef Platform =
3193 AvailabilityAttr::canonicalizePlatformName(GivenPlatform);
3194
3195 if (AvailabilityAttr::getPrettyPlatformName(Platform).empty()) {
3196 Diag(PlatformIdentifier->Loc,
3197 diag::err_avail_query_unrecognized_platform_name)
3198 << GivenPlatform;
3199 return None;
3200 }
3201
3202 return AvailabilitySpec(Version, Platform, PlatformIdentifier->Loc,
3203 VersionRange.getEnd());
3204 }
3205}

3207ExprResult Parser::ParseAvailabilityCheckExpr(SourceLocation BeginLoc) {
3208 assert(Tok.is(tok::kw___builtin_available) ||
3209 Tok.isObjCAtKeyword(tok::objc_available));
3210
3211 // Eat the available or __builtin_available.
3212 ConsumeToken();
3213
3214 BalancedDelimiterTracker Parens(*this, tok::l_paren);
3215 if (Parens.expectAndConsume())
3216 return ExprError();
3217
3218 SmallVector<AvailabilitySpec, 4> AvailSpecs;
3219 bool HasError = false;
3220 while (true) {
3221 Optional<AvailabilitySpec> Spec = ParseAvailabilitySpec();
3222 if (!Spec)
3223 HasError = true;
3224 else
3225 AvailSpecs.push_back(*Spec);
3226
3227 if (!TryConsumeToken(tok::comma))
3228 break;
3229 }
3230
3231 if (HasError) {
3232 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
3233 return ExprError();
3234 }
3235
3236 CheckAvailabilitySpecList(*this, AvailSpecs);
3237
3238 if (Parens.consumeClose())
3239 return ExprError();
3240
3241 return Actions.ActOnObjCAvailabilityCheckExpr(AvailSpecs, BeginLoc,
3242 Parens.getCloseLocation());
3243}
